# Performance tuning — the four knobs

| Config | Controls | Default |
|---|---|---|
| **`spark.sql.shuffle.partitions`** | partitions after shuffle | **200** |
| `spark.default.parallelism` | RDD default partitions | # cores |
| `spark.executor.memory` / `.driver.memory` | heap per executor / driver | cluster |
| **`spark.sql.autoBroadcastJoinThreshold`** | auto-broadcast max | 10 MB |

## The exam question

> "200 GB shuffling across 200 partitions, tasks **spilling to disk** — what changes?"

- Raise **`shuffle.partitions`** → each partition **100–200 MB**
- Too few → spill/OOM · too many → tiny empty tasks
- **AQE** (module 08) coalesces shuffle partitions **automatically**
